  "buggy_files": ["drivers/acpi/video_detect.c"],
  "buggy_functions": ["video_detect_dmi_table"],
  "confidence": 0.9,
  "reasoning": "The Acer TravelMate 5735Z laptop is missing from the video_detect_dmi_table in video_detect.c. The default behavior of acpi_video_get_backlight_type() returns acpi_backlight_video for this system, which causes the ACPI video backlight (_BCM/_BCL methods) to be used. However, the ACPI video backlight control does not actually work for this hardware. The native Intel GMA backlight driver is what correctly controls the brightness. The fix requires adding a DMI entry to the video_detect_dmi_table to force the system to use native backlight (acpi_backlight_native) instead of ACPI video backlight. The matching criteria should be sys_vendor='Acer' and product_name='TravelMate 5735Z', with callback=video_detect_force_native."
}

